# Let the unprivileged weaver daemon run privileged work as root — but only by exec'ing
# the solo-provisioner CLI, never raw tools. The daemon never shells out to
# kubectl/helm/kubeadm/systemctl (Kubernetes via client-go, systemd via dbus), so there are
# deliberately no raw-binary entries; re-adding them would grant root-equivalent access for
# no consumer. The whole binary is granted (any subcommand) because each delegated action
# maps to a different subcommand and the set is still growing — enumerating them would couple
# this template to in-progress daemon code.
#
# Blast radius: any weaver-group member can run any subcommand as root, including destructive
# ones — weaver-group membership is effectively root here. Still tighter than raw tool access
# (surface is the signed CLI, not arbitrary kubectl/systemctl). See "Security posture" in
# docs/dev/daemon/daemon-architecture.md.
#
# Both bare and "<path> *" forms are needed: a trailing * requires >=1 argument, so the
# no-arg invocation must be permitted separately.
weaver ALL=(root) NOPASSWD: /opt/solo/weaver/bin/solo-provisioner, \
  /opt/solo/weaver/bin/solo-provisioner *, \
  /usr/local/bin/solo-provisioner, \
  /usr/local/bin/solo-provisioner *
